(91, 3, '2017-11-06 13:08:49', '2017-11-06 13:08:49', '<p align=\"justify\"><span class=\"main\">Structural Repair For Beams, Columns And Slab Etc.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<div align=\"justify\">\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">Removing loose plaster, removing decayed, cracked Portion of Plaster and R.C.C. area with light hammering i.e. only cracked applying a coat of Polymer + Cement To the entire surface of R.C.C. with thick slurry.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">Providing and applying mix of Polymer + Cement + Dry sand 1: 2: 3 for preparing of filling putty in cracked R.C.C. Portion and giving the new life to the R.C.C. Area whatever is taken out by breaking.</li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"text\">After filling the crack with putty in path and cracks providing and applying mix of Polymer + Cement + Polymer grains in past applying by land in slurry form.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><span class=\"main\">Plastering Above Rcc Treatment </span>\r\n<span class=\"main\">\r\nOR Structural Repair :</span>\r\n<span class=\"text\">After RCC repair cleaning the surface treating The edges with One coat of Polymer + Cement. Providing and applying sand faced cement plaster Using approved Screened river sand first coat in 1:4 and second coat in 1: 5 cement mortar with even textured finish including all curing etc., Complete.</span></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><span class=\"main\">Structural Repair For Jacketing The Column Of Beams :</span>\r\n<span class=\"text\">Structural strengthening by required “I” section beams By proper gage with the decision of the committee and The proper inspection for required “I” section where it Is required after breaking the existing column, welding The R C.C. structure with existing old reinforcement Jacketing the “I” beams with the proper support etc., Filling the “I” section by M200 mix.\r\nNOTE: Required R.C.C. “I” section material to be supplied free of coat.</span></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><span class=\"main\">Polymer Repair For Water Tank Of Flooring And Walls Etc.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<div align=\"justify\">\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">Removing loose plaster, removing decayed, cracked Portion of plaster upto R.C.C. or brick work area.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">Removing the dust from R.C.C. wall Applying water and cleaning with water, applying One coat of polymer + cement applying as a Bond coat.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">Providing and applying mix of Polymer + Cement + Dry sand 1 : 2 : 3 . Filling the same putty in cracked R.C.C. porion brick column joints.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">After filling the cracks with putty in patch or cracks Providing and applying mix of Polymer + Cement + Polymer grains in past brushing first coat in vertical And applying second coat in horizontal.\r\n<p align=\"justify\"></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<strong>Repairing For External Walls Only The Surface Cracks And The Leakage</strong>\r\nErecting the scaffolding for the required height without damaging the external walls opening the surface cracks by cutting machine. Treating the cracks with water cleaning and waiting the surface applying and filling the cracks with polymer putty and applying one coat of polymer + polymer grains + same colour pigment coating to the entire required surface removing the scaffolding and curing for two days.\r\n\r\n<strong>Bathroom doorframe leakages :</strong>\r\nInspecting the toilets bathroom etc. complete and Giving proper idea for required treatment for w.c. And bathroom area. Per building RS. 1000/- (Only Inspection Charges)\r\n\r\nAfter Inspection if required door frame bottom has To be change because of the leakage. (One door cost RS. 500/-) cutting the doorframe bottom around 4 Inch. Ht. And grouting the same pocket with grouting with Cement polymer + sand finishing the door frame a Required as existing.\r\n\r\n<strong>Casting Parapet Wall :</strong>\r\nProviding second class 9” Brick masonary in CM (1:5) Including taking out joints ¾” deep in perfect Horizontal layers watering, curing etc. complete.\r\n\r\nProviding RCC putty 4” thick on top of parapet wall Level in proportion of 1: 2 : 4 to proper shape including Placing of Reinforcement framework, ramming , Watering etc. complete.\r\n\r\nSand faced cement plaster in one coat in proportionate Of 1 : 3 on both sides including smooth finish, watering, Curing etc. complete.\r\n\r\n<strong>Replacing Rcc Ventilator :</strong>\r\nProviding and fixing RCC ventilator of rectangular Shape of approved quality and design in the brick work\r\n\r\nReplacing Doors At Staircase Room :\r\nLabour charges for removing existing door from at Entrance of terrace and providing and fixing a new door Including finishing of side wall, plaster etc. complete.\r\n\r\n<strong>PARAPET WALL REPAIR JOB.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Breaking :</strong>\r\nBreaking Plaster of existing old Parapet wall for the Required height with lower down the debris and shifting to the required place.\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><span class=\"main\"><strong>ROUND WATTA FOR PARAPET TOP :</strong>\r\n</span>\r\n<span class=\"main\">The treatment consists following :</span></p>\r\n\r\n<div align=\"justify\">\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"text\">After dismantling the existing parapet top and removing dismantled material as directed and carting away the same.</span></li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">Providing the laying waterproofing agent on the Surface mixing with cement.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">The brick bat coba is covered with jointless water- Proof layer finished smooth with trowel</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">Carrying out the same treatment along the inner Side of parapet and / or other adjoining wall upto wata And outer side of wall upto beam &amp; slab jection level.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div align=\"right\"></div>\r\n<p class=\"text\" align=\"justify\">The average thickness of the waterproofing treatment For parapet top 2” half round and carryout the same plaster from wata level to external beam level with ‘V’ cracks opening Roundwata Con’t.</p>\r\n\r\n<div align=\"justify\">\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">Removing loose cracked plaster, removing decayed, cracked portion of plaster upto R.C.C. or block work area.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">Removing the dust from bricks or R.C.C. wall applying water and cleaning with water, applying one coat of polymer + cement applying as a bond coat.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">Providing and applying mix of Polymer + Cement + Dry sand 1: 2: 3. Filling the same putty in Cracked R.C.C. Portion and Bricks and Columns joints.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">After filling the cracks with putty in patch in cracks providing and fixing nipples inside the wall groves and then giving injection to the structures to take out air and to stop the corrosion and leakage. Filling the grout into the cavities in the form of grout. Mix of grout is Polymer + Cement and water to fill the cracks cavities by using 4 to 5 Kg. Pressure by slurry pump and the\r\nrequired injection to be paid separately as per rate grouting item per pressure grout hole\r\nThe same finishing the patch in two coats of plastering with watering the surface, edges should be treated with one coat of polymer + Cement using approved screened rive sand first coat in 1 : 4 25 mm and second coat in\r\n1 :5 cement mortar with even textured finish including all curing etc., complete.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong><span class=\"main\">Kitchen : </span></strong>\r\n<span class=\"text\">Removing the entire kitchen platform and Redoing the same with telephonic black granite fixing Still sink etc. complete.</span></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong><span class=\"main\">Kitchen Platform : </span></strong>\r\n<span class=\"text\">Removing the existing old kitchen platform carefully Avoding the breakage, breaking and opening the existing Stone, granite and stacking properly. Opening out the Tiles and finishing the existing surface by one coat of Plastering (Approximate Area 80.00 Sqft. for flooring and 300. 00 Sqft. for walls)</span></p>\r\nAs per the requirement fixing granite platform 2 to 2.5 ft. Width and 15 to 18 ft. in length, if required using the old Existing granite or using the new granite, fixing the Required partition, providing required molding and Finishing the same with the polishing , material includes Telephonic black granite, including all material sand, cement etc. Complete.\r\n<span class=\"text\">\r\nFixng the tiles for the required wall, fixing the tiles with All material with line and level finishing the joints with Required color pegment rate incluedes required tiles, sand\r\nCement, labour etc. complete. Fixng area, including flooring and wall.\r\nNote: Cost of the tiles is calculated @ 35.00 Rs. Per Sqft. If there is any cost verification of tiles, that will be borne by client.</span>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong><span class=\"main\">Furniture :</span> </strong>\r\n<span class=\"text\">Usign the old panels inside the drawers and preparing Drawer cabinet for kitchen platform for the required depth Of 2 and 2.5 ft. in depth for the requried kitchen platform\r\nUsing marine plywood and both the sides in the 1st quality Sunmica in the required color combination, including all Materila, ball bearing for drawer, marine ply, polishing\r\nEtc. complete.</span></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong><span class=\"main\">POLISHING THE MALAMUTE BY SPRAY MACHINE :</span></strong></p>\r\n<span class=\"main\">Polishing door panels and borders etc.</span>\r\n<div align=\"justify\">\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">Scrapping the entire door panels and borders.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">Coating one coat of primer.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">Scratching entire door panels and borders etc. with polishing putty.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text\">Finishing the polishing by hand.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\nFinishing the entire door panels and borders with malymate. Polishing by spray machine.\r\n\r\n<strong>Renovation Of Bathroom :</strong>\r\nBreaking the old existing toilet cloning as well as wall area, fixing the tiles on cloning and wall, fixing Indian or western W.C. fixing the doors frames etc., internally with Tiling fitting all fitting including wash basin with material labour etc., complete.\r\n\r\n<strong>Steel :</strong>\r\nCarting for steel cutting bending tying the Reinforcement to existing old reinforcement with the proper size and required gauge. Tying the reinforcement with wire and welding the same Steel with existing old reinforcement in a proper place cleaning the bar with rest-cleaner and keep opening for 24 hours for inspection.\r\n\r\n<strong>Bathroom :\r\n</strong><span class=\"text\">Breaking the entire bathroom taking out the plaster etc. Complete, coating one coat of plaster for wall area and Finishing and curing the same.</span>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong><span class=\"main\">Cudappa :</span></strong>\r\n<span class=\"text\">Fixing of cudappa on top of parapet wall. Removing the top plaster using cement mortar\r\nfor fixing cudappa filling the joints with polymer grout curing etc. complete. Providing and fixing polish cuddapa on the top of parapet wall</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"text\" align=\"justify\">Providing and fixing 20mm thick polish cuddapa stone 300 mm wide on the top parapet in terrace, bedding of C.M. (1: 4) 25mm thick slightly sloping inside the building. Joint of cuddapa sealing by leak proof sealent</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong><span class=\"main\">Pathways :</span></strong>\r\n<span class=\"text\">This is shown in site plan of the society. This consists of excavating to particular level, ramming, the base hand packing with minimum 9” Rubble to be kept vertical in trenches. All interstices shall be placed with small kapchis. All this shall be watered, rammed thoroughly, cement concrete of (1: 2: 4) proportion shall be laid on this of 4” to 6” depth, properly rammed. Regular side frames shall be erected to keep the concrete in position. After watering and curing the framework shall be taken out and spaces filled with murum and rammed again to society’s satisfaction. The level and proper slope shall be given as per society’s direction.</span></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong><span class=\"main\">P.O.P. :</span></strong>\r\n<span class=\"text\">Providing and applying Plaster of Paris coating for the entire wall including leveling required groove. Finishing entire wall with the line and level including all material etc., complete.</span></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong><span class=\"main\">False Sealing :</span></strong>\r\n<span class=\"text\">Fixing Aluminium brackets for the required area and fixing P.O.P. sheets leveling etc., complete. Coating the coat of Plaster of Paris on the top of the sheets. Preparing the false sealing with neat and clean.</span></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong><span class=\"main\">Acrylic false sealing for W.C. :</span></strong>\r\n<span class=\"text\">Fixing aluminium brackets for false sealing of W.C. Fixing the aluminium brackets with required squares. Placing decorative fiber sheet. Placing and fixing etc., complete.</span></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong><span class=\"main\">Plastering :</span></strong>\r\n<span class=\"text\">Breaking old cracked plaster upto brick or block work, cleaning the surface, treating the edges with one coat polymer + cement. Providing and applying sand faced plaster using approved screened sand (1:3) mixed with approved water-proofing compound @ 1 Kg. Per bag of cement. First scratch coat 14 mm thick followed by 6mm thick finish coat applied after curing scratch coat for 24 hours.</span></p>\r\n<strong> </strong>', 'Repair & Maintanance', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'repair-maintanance', '', '', '2017-11-07 11:52:14', '2017-11-07 11:52:14', '', 0, 'http://paintrepairconsultants.com/?page_id=91', 0, 'page', '', 0),
